36068370.review:
This is the game that introduced me to the franchise and is one of my fave games of the genre.

Pros:
- The gameplay is really interesting and fun; 
- Each character is unique when compared to others and they all have their own charm;
- The music is amazing;
- A helpful tutorial, for a change;
- It's really addicting;
- The story is great and quite different from the usual story modes from fighting games, it's really cool.
- Online multiplayer is always good.

Cons: 
- Getting to finish every character's Story and Arcade mode can be quite draining, sometimes it's better to just chill on versus or endless;
- It can be quite frustating at times (looking at you Hazama).

I would say this game is about 9/10.

21193244.review:
[h1]An awesome visual novel-ish heavy metal 2D fighting game[/h1]

A great [b]visual novel[/b] with English dub and a really convoluted yet interesting story... no, wait! I wanted to say [b]heavy metal album[/b]! N... no, wait. wait! I'm there! Exceptional [b]2D fighting game[/b]! Yes, this is it!
Okay, okay, not many people play fighting games for the plot... but BlazBlue: CSE could be the exception to the rule :3 

[b]PROS:[/b]
* smooth gameplay;
* amazing story (with optional "gag reels");
* unique characters (almost everyone of them has to be played in a different way);
* over-the-top finishers (the Moon is crumbling!);
* ridicolously good soundtrack (seriously, it would be worth the price even only for that);
* anti-stress features which transforms the gameplay from Street Fighter-like to Devil May Cry-like (stylish mode anyone?).

[b]CONS:[/b]
* certain characters require lot of time to master, especially for casual players like me (CAAAAAARL! YOU AND YOUR @#*§ DOLL!);
* stringing combos together and learning how to do the Distorsion / Astral Heat moves can be sometimes frustrating (again, only for the casual player) - but at least, it's rewarding when you are able to unleash a 20+ combo without having to use Stylish mode :3

Recommended? Absolutely yes if you love fighting games, anime, visual novel or metal music.

As a side note, [b][u]I would really recommend to play story mode, even if you are on the "competitive" side[/u][/b]: Terumi is one of the most well characterized manipulative bad guys I've ever found in a game. His speech lines are really unforgettable :)
